The output is an array of integers representing a permutation `perm` of length `n + 1`, where `n` is the length of the input string `s`.
The elements of the output array `perm` are integers in the range [0, n].
The output array `perm` satisfies the conditions specified by the input string `s`:
- If `s[i] == 'I'`, then `perm[i] < perm[i + 1]`.
- If `s[i] == 'D'`, then `perm[i] > perm[i + 1]`.
The output array `perm` is a valid permutation, meaning it contains all integers in the range [0, n] exactly once.
